(Earned Wage Access \(EWA\) Policy & Employee Acknowledgment) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Royal Lee Construction Solutions offers eligible employees access to Earned Wage Access) Tj
T*
(\(EWA\) as a voluntary financial wellness benefit. This program allows employees to access a) Tj
T*
(portion of wages they have already earned prior to the scheduled payroll date.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Program Overview) Tj
T*
(Earned Wage Access \(EWA\) enables employees to request and receive a portion of earned but) Tj
T*
(unpaid wages based on verified hours worked. EWA is not a loan and does not involve) Tj
T*
(interest. It is an advance on earned wages.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Eligibility Requirements) Tj
T*
(To participate in the EWA program, employees must:) Tj
T*
(- Be actively employed and in good standing) Tj
T*
(- Complete all required onboarding and payroll documentation) Tj
T*
(- Have accurately recorded and approved work hours) Tj
T*
(- Register and be approved through the company’s designated EWA provider) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. Access to Funds) Tj
T*
(- Employees may request access to earned wages after work hours have been completed and) Tj
T*
(  approved by management) Tj
T*
(- Access limits may apply based on total hours worked, company policy, and provider) Tj
T*
(  guidelines) Tj
T*
(- Funds may be delivered via direct deposit, debit card, or provider-supported transfer) Tj
T*
(  methods) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Fees and Charges) Tj
T*
(- Certain transactions, including instant transfers, may include fees charged by the EWA) Tj
T*
(  provider) Tj
T*
(- Standard transfer options may be available at no cost, depending on the provider) Tj
T*
(- Royal Lee Construction Solutions does not control or receive any portion of) Tj
T*
(  third-party fees) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Payroll Reconciliation) Tj
T*
(- Any wages accessed through the EWA program will be automatically deducted from the) Tj
T*
(  employee’s next scheduled paycheck) Tj
T*
(- Payroll statements will reflect all EWA transactions, deductions, and remaining net) Tj
T*
(  pay) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(6. Employee Responsibility) Tj
T*
(By enrolling in the EWA program, employees acknowledge and agree that:) Tj
T*
(- They are responsible for managing their wage access and personal financial planning) Tj
T*
(- Early access to wages will reduce their future paycheck amounts) Tj
T*
(- Abuse, misuse, or policy violations may result in suspension or termination of EWA) Tj
T*
(  access) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(7. Voluntary Participation) Tj
T*
(Participation in the EWA program is entirely voluntary. Employees are not required to enroll) Tj
ET
endstream
